notesStmt.note: Edges of some leaves are brittle and show previous insect damage. Leaves were closely cropped in binding, cutting off some decoration and marginal notes in a later hand.

msContents.summary: Begins with the psalms, but lacks the beginning and the end; with 2 items in slightly later hands on the last 3 folios: prayers (f. 159), and Vigilia mortuorum (f. 160-161).

supportDesc.extent: 161 leaves : 94 x 75 (71 x 53) mm. bound to 100 x 78 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Parchment, i (modern paper) + 161 + i (modern paper); [1-161]; modern foliation in pencil, lower right recto.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 15 long lines; frame-ruled in ink.

decoDesc.decoNote: Rubricated throughout, with red and blue capitals, 2-line alternating red and blue initials with contrasting red or blue ornamentation, 4-line and 6-line puzzle initials in red and blue with detailed ornamentation (f. 9r, 10r, 29r, 53r, 74r, 77r, and 97r).

binding.p: 19th-century calf, rebacked, splitting along back cover; remains of clasp.

origin.p: Written in Germany[?], in the late 14th century (Zacour-Hirsch).

history.provenance: Franz Graf von [undeciphered] 1830 and pencilled note of purchase 1809, inside back cover. (From Zacour-Hirsch Catalogue, these notes are no longer visible due to repair of the binding.)
